The paper focuses on identifying security-related commits in open-source projects using deep learning models. This involves analyzing code and identifying potential vulnerabilities, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR) categories. The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical deep learning models and regularization techniques, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper specifically focuses on Java code, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) category.
